{"Body":"<p>I noticed a similarity between the word <em><strong>Salut</strong></em> in French and the word <em><strong>سلام</strong></em> in Arabic which is pronounced <em><strong>Salaam</strong></em> and they both mean \"safety and well-being\" and are both used as a general greeting to mean \"hello\". But Salut comes from Latin which I don't think is related to Arabic in any way. How can that be possible then? </p>\n", "Id":"3208", "LastEditorUserId":"1768", "FavoriteCount":"2", "AcceptedAnswerId":"3209", "Title":"Similarity between Salut in French and Salaam in Arabic", "CreationDate":"2013-02-16T20:21:58.870", "OwnerUserId":"1768", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<french><arabic>", "AnswerCount":"3", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2013-02-18T08:37:03.127", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"5", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"1768", "AccountId":"2301206", "Views":"0", "Reputation":"80", "CreationDate":"2013-02-16T20:05:59.787", "DisplayName":"Mohammad Sanei", "LastAccessDate":"2013-12-28T15:12:50.363"}, "ViewCount":"238", "LastActivityDate":"2013-02-18T08:37:03.127", "Score":"2", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"5", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"1768", "AccountId":"2301206", "Views":"0", "Reputation":"80", "CreationDate":"2013-02-16T20:05:59.787", "DisplayName":"Mohammad Sanei", "LastAccessDate":"2013-12-28T15:12:50.363"}}